block.documentation:
The Quality Assurance Subsystem ensures that the fiber production process adheres to strict quality standards throughout its operation. Equipped with a comprehensive array of sensors, the QA subsystem monitors key environmental conditions such as temperature, vibration, and process anomalies. Temperature Sensors and Vibration Sensors provide real-time data to prevent conditions that could negatively impact fiber quality, such as overheating or unwanted mechanical movements. Meanwhile, the Process Monitoring Camera captures high-resolution images and video of the production process, allowing for visual detection of any physical defects in the fiber as it is drawn.
In addition to environmental monitoring, the Spectroscopy Sensor plays a vital role in maintaining fiber quality by analyzing the optical properties of the ZBLAN fiber in real-time. This sensor detects any internal inconsistencies or defects that could affect the fiber's performance. The Defect Detection CSC works in conjunction with the spectroscopy and visual data to automatically flag defects and provide feedback to the Process Control CSC for potential adjustments. Moreover, the Production Data Logging CSC tracks all parameters throughout the manufacturing process, ensuring that any anomalies are recorded for post-production analysis, and allowing for traceability of production batches. This level of quality assurance is essential for meeting the stringent requirements of high-performance optical fibers like ZBLAN.
